 to fulfil their pride related to =\r\ndoing good\n &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; religious work. So many people clung to Vivekanan=\r\nda and other monastic &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; disciples of Ramakrishna. If one expect=\r\ns something back from such &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; followers, well-wishers and discip=\r\nles (e.g. admiration, learning well, &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; spreading knowledge or m=\r\nessage in the world, giving money for the &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; religious order, et=\r\nc), there is no difference really between wife and &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; children a=\r\nnd them. In other words, attachment can form and bind you.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt; What binds you is your attitude towards people and your expectati=\r\nons &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; from people and NOT how much people like you and how atta=\r\nched THEY are &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; to you. To be free, you do not need people to &quot;=\r\nleave you free&quot;. You &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; can be surrounded by thousands of people=\r\n who are attached to you &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; heavily and yet you can be free. The=\r\nir attachment binds *them*. To be &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; free, have no attachment an=\r\nd no\n expectations. Give other whatever your &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; body, mind and s=\r\noul allow you to give. Have no expctations of getting &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; anythyi=\r\nng back. Take whatever comes back by itself. Simple!&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &=\r\ngt; * * *&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; When you fall sick You will be temp=\r\nted to go in for their help and &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt; vice versa.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;Vice versa&quot; is not a problem. Taking care of a sick person if=\r\n one is &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; able to, whether it is wife or parents or children or=\r\n someone else, is &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; not binding. If there is an expectation of =\r\na return favor, THEN it is &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; binding.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;=\r\n Regarding taking help: Expecting anything from anyone causes bondage, &lt;BR&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt; but taking what comes by itself, with neither excitement nor regr=\r\net, &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; does not cause bondage. Ma Sarada nicely demonstrated thi=\r\ns once.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; When Swami Yogananda was badly sick, Ma\n =\r\nSarada asked his erstwhile &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; wife (before sannyasa!) to come an=\r\nd serve him. That is so &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; unconventional! Swami Yogananda prote=\r\nsted saying it will set a bad &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; example. But Swami Yogananda di=\r\nd not have any expectations and this &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; was done voluntarily by =\r\nhis wife (or under the instruction of Ma &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; sarada, but not due =\r\nto any expectations or pressure from Yogananda). &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; After Yogana=\r\nnda overcame his reservations, he was neither excited nor &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; reg=\r\nretful. He accepted the service equanomously and not worrying about &lt;BR&gt;&gt=\r\n; &gt; what others will think or say.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; In fact, if=\r\n one puts pressure on oneself and wants to prove to the &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; world=\r\n how good one&#39;s renunciation us, THAT may be an attachment. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;=\r\nExpecting&quot; the world to see one&#39;s renunciation and appreciate one (or &lt;BR&gt;&=\r\ngt; &gt; not criticize one) is a very subtle attachment. Ma Sarada\n may hav=\r\ne &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; detected a subtle attachment and put Swami Yogananda in a s=\r\npot &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; intentionally and made him overcome the attachment. Great=\r\n teachers &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; like Ramakrishna and Ma Sarada teach subtle and val=\r\nuable lessons in a &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; practical way. It may not even be obvious =\r\nto onlookers that there was &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; a lesson there! This is how sadgu=\r\nrus operate..&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; * * *&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Bei=\r\nng able to renounce wife, children, parents, siblings, house, car &lt;BR&gt;&gt; =\r\n&gt; etc is a great thing. But, if one thinks that those are &quot;all &lt;BR&gt;&gt; =\r\n&gt; connections and ties&quot; that bind one, one is badly mistaken. Those are =\r\n&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; the gross ones - the external ones. The biggest bondage is in=\r\nternal. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; The identification with a body and identification wit=\r\nh a subtle &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; individual identity (e.g. the notion that one is N=\r\narasimha, an &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; engineer, a scholar, an\n astrologer etc) are muc=\r\nh stronger bondages &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; than any others.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt=\r\n; If one&#39;s hands or legs are cut off or if a tiger is eating one alive &lt;BR&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt; or if one is suffering from a terrible disease, can one focus the=\r\n mind &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; on god and not think of the body and its suffering? If =\r\none thinks &quot;*I* &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; am suffering&quot; and starts weeping, is one real=\r\nly free?&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; If someone praises a sannyasin for his r=\r\nenunciation, devotion to god, &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; wisdom or spiritual attainment,=\r\n will no sannyasin feel even a little &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; pride? If so, is one re=\r\nally free?&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; If a sannayasin does sadhana and exper=\r\niences some special things or &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; gets some siddhis, will it not =\r\ngive a little bit of pride or &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; satisfaction? If so, is one rea=\r\nlly free?&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Focusing so heavily on external renunci=\r\nation and making external &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;\n objects of attachment seem like a =\r\nmajor thing, while ignoring the real &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; attachment inside one (t=\r\nhe sense of &quot;this is I&quot; and &quot;these are mine&quot;), &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; is like beatin=\r\ng up a tiger cub and feeling proud of the achievement, &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; while =\r\nignoring the big tiget just lurking behind one and waiting to &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;=\r\n pounce on one!&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; * * *&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; L=\r\net me say one thing clearly. Sannyasa or external renunciation is an &lt;BR&gt;&g=\r\nt; &gt; *attempt* to cut oneself off from a few external objects that cause=\r\n &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; temptation (and bondage!) internally. It is not a guarantee =\r\nthat &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; internal temptations and bondages are completely destroy=\r\ned. The real &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; bondage comes from the internal attachment and n=\r\not from the external &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; objects. Work hard on removing it. Do no=\r\nt despise the external objects &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; or see them as &quot;leeches&quot; or be=\r\ncome fed up with them.&lt;BR&gt;&gt;\n &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Best regards,&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt=\r\n; Narasimha&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; --------------------------------------------------=\r\n--------&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish =\r\nWritings,&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and =\r\nPitri Tarpana:&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Fil=\r\nms that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFilms.org&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Spiritual=\r\nity: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Jyotish writin=\r\ngs: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Twitter ID: =\r\n@homam108&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; ----------------------------------------------------=\r\n------&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; On Fri, Jun 3, 2011 at 2:00 PM, chaudhuri.=\r\nkrishnendu wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; Sannyasa has got its own glory =\r\nand advantages! The freedom of a &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; sannyasin can hardly be desc=\r\nribed. Only a sannyasin can entirely cut &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; off all connections =\r\nand ties. Though you\n have colored your heart, &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; still all memb=\r\ners of your family will cling to you like leeches till &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; the en=\r\nd of your life. You cannot entirely eradicate moha or infatuated &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &=\r\ngt; love and attachment for your family. When you fall sick You will be &lt;BR=\r\n&gt;&gt; &gt; tempted to go in for their help and vice versa. The old samskara=\r\ns will &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; get a new life and moha will bind you with stronger ch=\r\nains once again. &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; It is only when you take sannyasa that they =\r\nwill leave you free. They &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; will leave all hopes which they had=\r\n on you. Only then you become dead &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; for them. They will not ap=\r\nproach you again.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;STYLE type=3Dtext=\r\n/css&gt;\n&lt;!--\n#ygrp-mkp {\nborder:1px solid #d8d8d8;font-family:Arial;margin:10=\r\npx 0;padding:0 10px;}\n\n#ygrp-mkp hr {\nborder:1px solid #d8d8d8;}\n\n#ygrp-mkp=\r\n #hd {\ncolor:#628c2a;font-size:85%;font-weight:700;line-height:122%;margin:=\r\n10px 0;}\n\n#ygrp-mkp #ads {\nmargin-bottom:10px;}\n\n#ygrp-mkp .ad {\npadding:0 =\r\n0;}\n\n#ygrp-mkp .ad p {\nmargin:0;}\n\n#ygrp-mkp .ad a {\ncolor:#0000ff;text-dec=\r\noration:none;}\n#ygrp-sponsor #ygrp-lc {\nfont-family:Arial;}\n\n#ygrp-sponsor =\r\n#ygrp-lc #hd {\nmargin:10px 0px;font-weight:700;font-size:78%;line-height:12=\r\n2%;}\n\n#ygrp-sponsor #ygrp-lc .ad {\nmargin-bottom:10px;padding:0 0;}\n\na {\nco=\r\nlor:#1e66ae;}\n\n#actions {\nfont-family:Verdana;font-size:11px;padding:10px 0=\r\n;}\n\n#activity {\nbackground-color:#e0ecee;float:left;font-family:Verdana;fon=\r\nt-size:10px;padding:10px;}\n\n#activity span {\nfont-weight:700;}\n\n#activity s=\r\npan:first-child {\ntext-transform:uppercase;}\n\n#activity span a {\ncolor:#508=\r\n5b6;text-decoration:none;}\n\n#activity span span {\ncolor:#ff7900;}\n\n#activit=\r\ny span .underline